          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "ATP-dependent specificity component of the Clp protease. It directs the protease to specific substrates. Can perform chaperone functions in the absence of ClpP"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the ClpX chaperone family"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBUNIT",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Component of the ClpX-ClpP complex. Forms a hexameric ring that, in the presence of ATP, binds to fourteen ClpP subunits assembled into a disk-like structure with a central cavity, resembling the structure of eukaryotic proteasomes"
            }
          ]
